The main themes taught and discussed during the course: 
The nature of youth work and main concepts. 
The structure of Estonian youth work. 
The frame documents of youth work in Estonia and on European level. 
The main institutions related to youth work. 
The quality of youth work and the professional ethics of a youth worker.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aim is to give overview of the concept, formation and present situation of the youth work in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student will: - understand the nature of youth work and its current position; - orientates between and within the concepts of youth work; - knows regulations of youth work; - knows the professional ethics of youth workers; - knows the youth work institutions, networks and partners; - knows how to use information sources related to youth work. - can define the need and goals of informal education and lifelong learning; - can carry out reflective analysis of oneself as youth worker.
